        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> @mikejmcguirk Probably not, depends on what information is wanted I guess? I added a comment below where you can get the coordinates of the selection pretty easily.\r\n\r\nTo me this makes sense. It's enough to experiment with, but avoids major code changes based on what might end up being speculation.\r\n\r\nEDIT: One issue could be - If this change is backported, that implies a level of commitment about what the public function returns. If this isn't the right place to make that decision, then I'd be fine making a follow-up issue to think through it more thoroughly.",
